        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:59PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 558 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Earlville, or 8 miles northeast of Mendota, moving east at 25 mph.
This storm may also be capable of producing funnel clouds.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, pea size hail, and possible funnel
clouds .

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Earlville and Leland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
